Still united! Jennifer Garner and Ben Affleck take their kids out for sweets five months after split... but neither actor has filed for divorce yet 
By

Heidi Parker For Dailymail.com


Published:
  14:19 EDT, 14 November 2015

 | 
Updated:
  01:40 EDT, 15 November 2015














e-mail








238
shares

 
         123
View  comments



It's been five months since Jennifer Garner and Ben Affleck announced their split.And still neither has filed for divorce yet.On Saturday the 43-year-old actors continued to put on a united front as they took all three children out to Cake Mix in LA for some sweets. Neither wore their wedding rings.Scroll down for video   





 Still putting on a united front: Jennifer Garner and Ben Affleck took all three children out to Cake Mix in LA for some sweets on Saturday; in this shot they are seen with Seraphina and Samuel  





 Dressed down: Jennifer looked nautical chic in her blue and white striped sweater and jeans with white sneakers. Ben had on a blue blazer over a plaid shirt over a blue T, jeans and shiny shoes. The kids were dressed casually in tops, shorts and sneakers; that's Violet on the left in pinkJennifer looked nautical chic in her blue and white striped sweater and jeans with white sneakers.Ben had on a blue blazer over a plaid shirt over a blue T, jeans and shiny shoes. He was clean shaven.The kids were dressed casually in tops, shorts and sneakers.  





 They both work so much: Affleck has been filming a movie in Georgia while Garner just finished making Miracles From Heaven there  





 Good daddy: The Boston native with daughter Violet; here he put on a burgundy cap  





 Hard at work: Ben has been filming the 1920s set drama Live By Night in Georgia; he not only stars in it, but he also directsIn August, GossipCop reported that Ben and Jennifer are not getting back together.It was added that the two have yet to file for divorce because they are mediating in private.And once they are done with that process, they will alert the courts.The two seem to be moving ahead slowly with sorting out their assets. It was only last month that Jennifer listed their palatial Pacific Palisades property for $45 million, according to Variety.  





 Hands on mama: The Pearl Harbor star has another movie in the works, Nine Lives with Kevin Spacey  





 On track: In August, GossipCop reported that Ben and Jennifer are not getting back together. It was added that the two have yet to file for divorce because they are mediating in private  





 No rush: The two seem to be moving ahead slowly with sorting out their assets. It was only last month that Jennifer listed their palatial Pacific Palisades property for $45 million, according to Variety 





 





No bling: Neither actor wore their wedding bands; they have said in the past they wore them for the kids






Earlier on Saturday the Alias vet smiled as she picked up an iced coffee in the Brentwood neighborhood of Los Angeles. The mother even took a moment to pet a cute little dog that was tied up outside the Italian cafe. The actress wore a light grey top and black Nike capri leggings with very bright blue and purple sneakers.Garner also had her hair pulled back into a messy ponytail and wore little jewelry except for her silver watch.With the stunner was her blonde friend, who she is often seen heading to workouts with.  





 No tears: Jennifer Garner looks pretty happy for a woman going through a divorce. On Saturday morning the 43-year-old Alias vet smiled as she picked up an iced coffee in the Brentwood neighborhood of Los Angeles  





 OK with me: This summer the beauty split from husband of 10 years, Ben Affleck, though neither has filed for divorce yet  





 Cutie: The mother of three even took a moment to pet a cut little dog that was tied up outside the cafeAfter leaving the cafe, Jennifer noticed the dog, which was medium sized and beige. He was tied to a bench by a purple leash.She looked thrilled to spot the furry little guy, who had one leg sticking out.And then the Catch And Release star leaned down to touch his head.  





 Hey there little one: After leaving the cafe, Jennifer noticed the dog, which was medium sized and beige. She looked thrilled to spot the furry little guy  





 She made contact: And then the Catch And Release star leaned down to touch his head  





 Chic for a workout: The actress wore a light grey top and black Nike capri leggings. She also had her hair pulled back into a messy ponytail and wore little jewelry except for her silver watchGarner was last seen on Friday with her daughter Seraphina.The Pearl Harbor star seemed in high spirits indeed as she pounded the pavement with her six-year-old sidekick.Again, she smiled and appeared very friendly, which has become her trademark.  





It beats acting: Garner looked like she was having a great time with daughter Seraphina in Los Angeles on FridayThe star wore a light and bright ensemble of star-filled blue woollen sweater, jeans and sensible flat leather shoes.She was also looking remarkably fresh-faced, with her flawlessly flat forehead really catching the eye.This is especially the case as it had been so remarkably crinkled on Monday, where her heavily arched eyebrows made her look extremely surprised, despite the fact she was making a routine stop for a workout session.   





 Garner-ing attention: All eyes were on the saucy starlet's remarkably wrinkle-free forehead  





 She's Elektra-fying: The youngster seemed full of energy as she skipped along the pavement

































